    <section id="accessibility">
        <h2 class="quando">Accessibility Policy</h2>

        <div class="container">
        <p>Plumify is committed to making its site accessible to all users, including people with disabilities. We follow the recommendations of Web Accessibility Standards (WCAG) to ensure that our content is available and usable by as many people as possible.</p>
        <h3>Accessibility Improvements</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> The site is designed to be navigable by keyboard, allowing easy access without a mouse.</li>
            <li><strong>Screen Reader Compatibility:</strong> Plumify is optimized to work with major screen reading software.</li>
            <li><strong>Contrast:</strong> Colors are selected for high contrast to improve readability.</li>
            <li><strong>Alt Text:</strong> Alternative descriptions are provided for all important images.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If you experience any access difficulties with our site, please contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@plumify.com">contact@plumify.com</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section id="privacy">
        <h2 class="quando">Personal Data Protection (GDPR)</h2>
        <div class="container">
        <p>Plumify attaches great importance to the protection of your personal data. We comply with European regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>

        <h3>1. Data Collection</h3>
        <p>We only collect the information necessary to provide you with an optimal user experience, such as your name, email address, and information related to your book loans. This data is collected during your registration and when you use our services.</p>

        <h3>2. Data Usage</h3>
        <p>Your personal data is used for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Managing your user account.</li>
            <li>Managing book loans and reservations.</li>
            <li>Improving our service.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties without your consent.</p>

        <h3>3. Data Security</h3>
        <p>Plumify implements security measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, disclosure, or alteration.</p>

        <h3>4. User Rights</h3>
        <p>In accordance with the GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Right of access:</strong> You can request access to your personal data.</li>
            <li><strong>Right of rectification:</strong> You can request the correction of your information if it is inaccurate.</li>
            <li><strong>Right to erasure:</strong> You can request the deletion of your personal data under certain conditions.</li>
            <li><strong>Right to object:</strong> You can object to the processing of your personal data for legitimate reasons.</li>
            <li><strong>Right to portability:</strong> You can obtain a copy of your personal data in a structured format.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise your rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@plumify.com">privacy@plumify.com</a>.</p>

        <h3>5. Data Retention Period</h3>
        <p>We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to achieve the purposes for which it was collected, unless the law requires a longer retention period.</p>

        <h3>6. Changes to Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p>Plumify reserves the right to modify this privacy policy. Any changes will be posted on this page and will take effect immediately.</p>

